The Silverfern Group




















Brooks J. Klimley
Managing Director




New York








Mission and Values
Our People
Our Investors
Risk Management




Brooks is a Managing Director of Silverfern and brings over 25 years of senior energy and natural resources experience to the Silverfern team, being well versed in virtually all facets of the conventional, alternative and renewable energy and power businesses, in addition to having significant transactional experience within and across all public and private debt, quasi-equity and equity markets. Based in New York, Brooks leads Silverfern‚Äôs global investments in the energy and natural resources sectors.
Prior to Silverfern, Brooks was President of CIT Energy, where he established a merchant banking business providing strategic advice and capital to energy and power companies in the U.S. Previously, Brooks held senior investment banking positions focused on global origination efforts in the energy and natural resources sectors at Citigroup, Bear Stearns, UBS Securities and Kidder, Peabody.
Brooks earned his dual BA/MA in Jurisprudence (Law) from Oxford University, where he studied under the auspices of the Euretta J. Kellet Research Fellowship, which he received from Columbia University.¬† He graduated from Columbia University magna cum laude and was elected to Phi Beta Kappa while jointly majoring in Economics and History. Brooks remains active at Columbia, where he is an Adjunct Professor at both Columbia University‚Äôs Business School and School of International and Public Affairs, where he teaches graduate level courses focused on the terms and applications of various financing structures developed in response to evolving industry, regulatory and market conditions.














Brooks J. Klimley: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 23, 2017 2:32 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of The Silverfern Group, Inc.



SnapshotPeople¬†




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Brooks J. Klimley  Managing Director, The Silverfern Group, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 2 different industries.See Board Relationships59--
Background

		Mr. Brooks J. Klimley serves as a Managing Director at The Silverfern Group, Inc. Mr. Klimley is responsible for leading global investments in the energy and natural resources sectors. He has over 25 years of senior experience in energy and natural resources, being well versed with all facets of conventional, alternative, renewable energy and power businesses, in addition to transactional experience within and across all public and private debt, quasi-equity and equity ... markets. Prior to firm, he served as a Managing Director at The Silverfern Group, Inc., Investment Banking Arm. Prior to that, Mr. Klimley served as an Adjunct Professor at Columbia University's Business School and School of International and Public Affairs since 2010, where he taught graduate level courses focused on the terms and applications of various financing structures developed in response to evolving industry, regulatory and market conditions. Prior to that, he served as the President at Brooks J. Klimley & Associates. Prior to that, Mr. Klimley served as the President at CIT Energy since 2005, where he was responsible for establishing the merchant banking business providing strategic advice and capital to energy and power companies in United States. Prior to that, he served as the Managing Director and Co-Head of Diversified Industrials Group at Citigroup Global Markets Inc. and Salomon Smith Barney, Inc. from 2001 to 2004, where he was responsible for global client management of large capitalization industrial companies. Prior to that, Mr. Klimley served as a Senior Managing Director and Co-Head of Natural Resources Group at Bear, Stearns & Co., Inc. from 1998 to 2001, where he was responsible for leading the origination and execution teams covering a broad range of natural resources companies. Prior to that, he served as the Managing Director and Co-Head of Natural Resources Group at Kidder, Peabody & Co. Inc. from 1984 to 1994. Prior to that, Mr. Klimley worked in Energy & Minerals Group at Chemical Bank from 1981 to 1984. He has been Director of AMGP GP LLC since May 09, 2017 and an Independent Director of Antero Midstream Partners LP since April 11, 2017 Previously, Mr. Klimley also served as a Director and President of Giant Industries, Inc. since August 16, 2002. He served as Director at Antero Midstream GP LP since April 11, 2017. Mr. Klimley received dual B.A./M.A. in Jurisprudence (Law) from the Oxford University and graduated in Economics and History, magna cum laude from the Columbia University, where he was elected to Phi Beta Kappa.Read Full Background




